title: [Bloodriven Village, Bailey Park]
description: The scent of pine is strong here, and the wall bordering the street is tacky with sap.  A gnarled tree trunk has pushed partly through the stone wall, its branches hugging the stones in an insistent embrace.  Beneath the canopy of needles stands the Bloodriven bank.

The scent of pine is strong here, and the wall bordering the street is tacky with sap, yet the cobblestones are slightly frozen over.  A gnarled tree trunk has pushed partly through the stone wall, its branches heavily laden with blown glass ornaments.  Beneath the canopy of glass stands the Bloodriven bank.
